<subSubSection id="2DD56497FFF2FFBFFF20FF3563F021D3" pageId="6" pageNumber="438" type="description">
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF2FFBFFF20FF35619023F4" blockId="6.[151,723,151,214]" box="[151,405,187,214]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">
(
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFF28FF35613423F7" box="[159,305,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Figs. 2. E–H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFE8BFF35618823F4" box="[316,397,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">4. G–L</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF2FFBFFF20FE8D6359223F" blockId="6.[151,1437,259,970]" box="[151,860,259,286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF2FFBFFF20FE8D6146223C" bold="true" box="[151,323,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Measurement.</emphasis>
Length of male including tegmen: 4.8–4.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF2FFBFFF70FEA96190228C" blockId="6.[151,1437,259,970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF2FFBFFF70FEA9614A2260" bold="true" box="[199,335,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Coloration.</emphasis>
Vertex pale yellowish, covered with dark brown reticulation; eyes grey; ocelli brown (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFA84FEA965952260" box="[1331,1424,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Face black (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFEA9FEC5617D2244" box="[286,376,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). Pronotum pale yellowish, marked with dark brown reticulation and yellowish brown patches. Scutellum pale yellowish with dark brown reticulation (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFCB0FEE1636422A8" box="[775,865,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Forewing subhyaline, with dense and dark brown reticulations (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFE86FE1D618D228C" box="[305,392,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF2FFBFFF70FE3964162138" blockId="6.[151,1437,259,970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF2FFBFFF70FE39616422F0" bold="true" box="[199,353,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Morphology.</emphasis>
Head declivous, slightly narrower than pronotum; ocelli on crown, between eyes with their distance about 4.0 times that of ocellus to adjacent eye (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFCBEFE55638F22D4" box="[777,906,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Figs. 2F, G</figureCitation>
). Postclypeus flat; anteclypeus slightly convex, truncate at apex (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFEEFFE7161B72138" box="[344,434,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). Scutellum 0.40 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFC1BFE7164032138" box="[940,1030,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[156,1415,319,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[151,1436,309,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–D Chanohirata plania A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and pronotum, dorsal view; D, face. E–H. Chanohirata yunnana E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and pronotum, dorsal view; H, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF2FFBFFF70FDAD63F021D3" blockId="6.[151,1437,259,970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF2FFBFFF70FDAD617C211C" bold="true" box="[199,377,547,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore lobes rounded caudally with short and long macrosetae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFAD8FDAD60BB2140" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular. Subgenital plate longer than length of pygofer, nearly triangular, with several short setae near the lateral margin and near apex (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFDF2FDE5629A21A4" box="[581,671,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
). Style apex cheliform with developed preapical lobe, lateral margin sinuate (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFF4DFD0161482188" box="[250,333,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
). Connective similar to ‘T’-shape, similar in length to style, arms shorter than stem (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFA8DFD01658A2188" box="[1338,1423,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Fig. 4J</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with dorsal ridge(poorly sclerotized wrinkled area) in lateral view, broad at base in ventral view, dorsal developed, preatrium small, gonopore on in ventral side (
<figureCitation id="FDF42B99FFF2FFBFFCD3FD5963ED21D3" box="[868,1000,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,188,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-31@7.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Chanohirata plania A, male genital capsule, lateral view; B, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C, style, ventral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, dorsal view; F, aedeagus, lateral view. G–L. Chanohirata yunnana G, male genital capsule, lateral view; H, genital valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; I, style, ventral view; J, connective, ventral view; K, aedeagus, ventral view; L, aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501299/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Figs. 4K, L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
