<subSubSection id="2DD56497FFF2FFBFFF70FCE961D82084" pageId="6" pageNumber="438" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6570371CFFF2FFBFFF70FCE961D82084" blockId="6.[151,1437,259,970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF2FFBFFF70FCE9614720A0" bold="true" box="[199,322,871,897]" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A2CF4C9FFFF2FFBFFDD7FCE662B820A0" baseAuthorityName="Matsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[608,701,871,898]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chanohirata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theae">
<emphasis id="57BBEB0EFFF2FFBFFDD7FCE662B820A0" box="[608,701,871,898]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="438">C. theae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the later by the aedeagal shaft with a dorsal ridge in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
